{% set pageTitle = "Find British Sign Language content" %}
{% set pageDescription = "The British Sign Language (BSL) icon helps BSL users recognise that information is available in BSL." %}
{% set pageSection = "Design system" %}
{% set subSection = "Patterns" %}
{% set theme = "Help users to" %}
{% set dateUpdated = "September 2025" %}
{% set backlog_issue_id = "547" %}

{% extends "layouts/app-layout.njk" %}

{% block beforeContent %}
  {% include "design-system/patterns/_breadcrumb.njk" %}
{% endblock %}

{% block bodyContent %}

<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-one-half nhsuk-u-one-half">
    {{ image({
      src: "/assets/BSL-icon-01.svg",
      classes: "app-image--border nhsuk-u-padding-6 nhsuk-u-margin-top-0",
      alt: "Two hands signing translation in British Sign Language, with the letters BSL beside"
    }) }}
  </div>
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-one-half nhsuk-u-one-half">
    {{ image({
      src: "/assets/BSL-icon-02.svg",
      classes: "app-image--border nhsuk-u-width-one-half nhsuk-u-padding-6 nhsuk-u-margin-top-0",
      alt: "Two hands signing translation in British Sign Language"
    }) }}
  </div>
</div>

<p>You can use it:</p>
<ul>
  <li>to signpost to BSL content or services</li>
  <li>next to content about a BSL service</li>
  <li>in video thumbnails</li>
</ul>

<p>Do not use the icon on its own without content to explain what it is.</p>
<p>Do not use "BSL" in written content without spelling out the abbreviation. For example, in a video description, explain "Includes British Sign Language (BSL) translation".</p>

<h2>Download the icons</h2>
<p>Download a zip folder containing the icons in SVG and PNG format.</p>

<div class="nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-4">
  {{ button({
    text: "Download BSL icons (2.13MB)",
    href: "/assets/bsl-icons.zip",
    preventDoubleClick: true
  }) }}
</div>

<h2>Feed back your findings</h2>
<p>We have tested the icon with BSL users but we need more information about:</p>
<ul>
  <li>how non-BSL users react to the icon as part of their user journey</li>
  <li>where BSL users expect to find the BSL icon as part of their user journey</li>
  <li>if the BSL icon is appropriate for signposting to both BSL translation and interpretation services (like BSL video relay services)</li>
</ul>

